examples.en: Margaret regarded her mother's peculiarities with a fond tolerance.
She was well aware of the peculiarity of her own situation.
It is a peculiarity of Asia that its regions are either very hot or very cold.
Scientists tried to explain some peculiarities in the results of the experiment.
It is a peculiarity of the house that there is no front door.
The lack of a written constitution is a peculiarity of the British political system.
